    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#mohamed-jmr1997"/>, pp. 32-33 n. <citedRange>1 A</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2177, A</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>085500</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>266</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.39</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀνδρίας">Ἀνδρίας</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀνάξιππος" type="patronymic">Ἀναξίπ<unclear>π</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <rdg resp="#mohamed-jmr1997">Ἀναξίπ<supplied reason="lost">π</supplied>ω</rdg>
                    </app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Andrias fils d'Anaxippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Andrias son of Anaxippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Andrias figlio di Anaxippos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This base comes from the same tomb, unrecorded by Cassels, as <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr085600</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr085700</ref> and was
                found during construction works in the new town of Shahat.</p>
	<p>As supposed by the editors, the three bases seem to mention men belonging to four generations in the same family.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
